{
  "stem": "23645.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the panic sort of subsided.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we go out in the other side.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You have a pile of clothes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And everybody scrams there to try and find something to fit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were no children, so, naturally, when I found a pair of pants, they came up to my-- to my neck, which was fine, in a way, because it kept me warm.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a jacket that was six times the size.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Who knows?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Probably-- what they did-- the Germans find out-- found out, you know, that there are gold and and silver that you can find in these clothes.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they had a group of people, inmates, that were ripping these apart, under their visual inspection.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so that's how they-- the pictures got destroyed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And what I am sorry about, and what I-- I'd give anything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Let them have the gold.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's not important.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's the pictures-- the pictures.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "What I wouldn't do to look at the face of my mum, who I adored, and the picture of my father and my brothers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I have one picture that somebody recognized after the war, when they walked on the street of Skarzysko, and they saw a picture of my oldest brother in uniform.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he recognized it and sent it to my sister and I.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's my treasure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When I look at it, I-- when I first got it, I looked at it for days!",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I couldn't-- you know, every day I'd look at it for-- and I'd look at it, stare at it, look at his eyes, look at his nose.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It's so precious-- a picture.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The Holocaust teaches us so many things about life and what's important and what isn't important.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
